            "id": "f92949425c24436898626",
            "questionText": "Calculate the average kinetic energy of a single water molecule at 100 $!$^{\\circ}$!$C, given that the Boltzmann constant is approximately 1.38 x 10^{-23} J/K. (Note: Use the absolute temperature corresponding to 100 $!$^{\\circ}$!$C in your calculation.)",
